lol, loved your &quot;putting the Dumb back in Dumbledore&quot;. Well, to answer
why this error was made, we naturally have to pull out the good, old
'thematic' card. JKR *had* to end the HP saga at Hogwarts. That was
the right decision from a thematic point of view. We had spent six
books coming to know and love the Hogwarts School of Witchcraft and
Wizardry. Like they said for sonatas in music during the Classical
era, you must begin at home (the exposition section), go away from
home (the development section) and then finally return home
(recapitulation section), to have the proper sonata structure play
out. Well, Hogwarts has been 'home' for HP, and for all his readers,
all of this time. To have the climactic showdown between evil and good
anywhere else would have been quite unthinkable. Notice how JKR made
the homecoming sweeter by having the core trio stay away from Hogwarts
for most of the duration of the book, so that when the catharsis of
going back to Hogwarts finally arrived toward the end, it gave us all
a high of getting to see the familair again.

So one of the Horcruxes *had* to be hidden at Hogwarts. Otherwise, why
would HP, Hermione and Ron go back there? Sure, if that forced JKR to
put the Dumb back in Dumbledore, that was just one of those
inconvenient somethings that she would have to live with.

